Words that cannot be translated into English
2018-12-18 [Facebook https://www.facebook.com/nishiohirokazu/posts/10217087543757279]
The [Sapir-Whorf hypothesis] that different languages can express different things, and that this affects the perceptions and thoughts of the people who use that language. I can't translate "[tulun]" into English, so using a word like that to describe things is a zoooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooong case.

Troon" is not in the dictionary, but even if it were in the dictionary, it is often the case that when people use a certain word X, it deviates from the dictionary definition ([(6.2.5.4) Checking with the dictionary] p.204).

